<br>
Who's buying an epic?<br>
<br>
Are you telling me, Dlgoth, that when you did your rogue epic, you personally camped the ghoul archmage for your SMR, then the coercer or Ishva Mal for the Ishva robe, then went to OOT and mugged that poor Oracle for his robe?<br>
<br>
If you didn't, stfu about me buying my epic.  If you did, you're a doofus.<br>
<br>
Maybe you got lucky and your general dropped a Cazic Quill.  If so, then good for you, and you aren't entitled to an opinion as to how I go about scoring the robes that you didn't even need in the first place.<br>
<br>
Honestly, people.  Wake the hell up and think before you type. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uaanadien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aanadien</A> at: 12/1/01 3:29:14 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uepiphanyeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Epiphany EQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(12/1/01 5:33:39 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.vanessarussell.com/Phank/epiavitarsmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: WTB: MQ Kedge Robe, SMR, Ishva, Oracle</span><hr size=1> At the risk of getting involved in a stupid flame fest, here goes.<br>
<br>
I bought an SMR which I later used for part of my epic (which I'm still working on).  So did I buy my epic?  <br>
<br>
The quest (any quest) is about seeking out the requirements and turning them in to the correct NPCs.  If you can find a better way to get them rather than endlessly camping green mobs then you're smart not lazy.  The game really isn't supposed to be about camping.  Do you seriously feel like you get more out of the game if you camp for stuff yourself?  If so, more power to you.  Leave those of us that prefer a slightly more interesting game alone.<br>
<br>
And while I'm at it think about this: What do all those lower level players think of you when you are camping mobs that would be xp, great loot, and a challenge for them?  Sure you need it for some quest, and you have every right to the mob.  But it sure would be more considerate of you to just toss the newbies some coin and let them camp it.  It's win-win.  You don't have to camp it, and you don't take away somebody else's spawns.<br>
<br>
There are 2 ways to get a kedge robe.  First, you can beg your friends to come with you to some god-forsaken underwater dungeon to kill some guy that nobody cares about at this level.  Second, you can find somebody else that killed him back when they did give a darn about him and help each other out.<br>
